1
00:00:00,916 --> 00:00:05,000
All the prisoners’ stories were sad

2
00:00:05,291 --> 00:00:07,708
Especially those whose children had been killed

3
00:00:07,916 --> 00:00:09,333
Or who had left orphans behind

4
00:00:10,541 --> 00:00:12,083
There was a young man named Abu Madian

5
00:00:12,416 --> 00:00:13,416
From the town of Mansoura

6
00:00:13,833 --> 00:00:18,000
We used to notice his written memories of his son

7
00:00:18,208 --> 00:00:20,708
In every solitary or group cell we passed through

8
00:00:20,875 --> 00:00:22,791
He would express his feelings and longing

9
00:00:22,916 --> 00:00:25,291
Madian, my dear, I never got enough of you, mourning his son

10
00:00:25,666 --> 00:00:27,916
As if he knew he would never see him again

11
00:00:28,291 --> 00:00:30,416
He was the one who made us feel the saddest

12
00:00:30,541 --> 00:00:32,291
Even though I never met him

13
00:00:32,375 --> 00:00:34,958
I’m still affected by him to this day

14
00:00:36,750 --> 00:00:39,625
Another young man was named Faisal Saad Rajoub

15
00:00:39,791 --> 00:00:40,791
From Homs

16
00:00:41,583 --> 00:00:44,750
He stayed under the siege of Homs even after his family left

17
00:00:45,041 --> 00:00:47,375
Resisting there for about four years

18
00:00:47,958 --> 00:00:50,166
He left through the United Nations

19
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:54,000
He tried every way to reach his mother but failed

20
00:00:54,166 --> 00:00:56,583
So he was forced to join ISIS

21
00:00:56,666 --> 00:01:00,416
He tried to go to Turkey to see her but couldn’t

22
00:01:01,250 --> 00:01:02,375
During his torture

23
00:01:04,166 --> 00:01:07,708
He kept screaming for his mother

24
00:01:07,916 --> 00:01:10,958
Begging her forgiveness because he couldn’t see her

25
00:01:11,083 --> 00:01:12,916
Or reach her

26
00:01:13,166 --> 00:01:15,958
While she was suffering from heart disease

27
00:01:16,625 --> 00:01:18,875
He was deeply affected by his mother’s condition

28
00:01:19,208 --> 00:01:21,416
His mind was preoccupied

29
00:01:22,625 --> 00:01:25,333
Thinking how his mother would
take the news of his death later
